Class SocialContract

Provides utility constant values for using SocialProvider.

Please read information about how to use content providers in Android in order to learn how to use this contract. You can start by going into this page at Android developers site.

Note that this contract is currently the only documentation of SocialProvider on Android.

Author:
Babak Farshchian

ACCOUNT_TYPE_LOCAL

public static final String ACCOUNT_TYPE_LOCAL
A special account type used for fields that are not supposed to be synced. See also SynchColumns. When you store something in a row that you don't want to be synced, set its ACCOUNT_TYPE to this.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

GLOBAL_ID_PENDING

public static final String GLOBAL_ID_PENDING
Is used when setting global ID for newly created rows. If the row is syncable the global ID has to be replaced with a proper global ID upon a successful first sync. If the row is private, the global ID will always be pending, i.e. it should not be used.

CALLER_IS_SYNCADAPTER

public static final String CALLER_IS_SYNCADAPTER
An optional insert, update or delete URI parameter that allows the caller to specify that it is a sync adapter.

The default value is false.

If set to true, the caller must also include ACCOUNT_NAME and ACCOUNT_TYPE as query parameters.
